<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="2" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[264,1325,1022,1889]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[264,392,1022,1048]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Head deeper than long, lateral cephalic lobe weak, ventrolateral flap welldeveloped. Epistome and upper lip fused. Antenna 
<number box="[901,919,1063,1089]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="2.0">2</number>
: peduncular article 
<number box="[1166,1181,1063,1089]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="1.0">1</number>
not greatly enlarged; peduncular article 
<number box="[600,615,1103,1129]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="3.0">3</number>
without a distal hook. Mandible: incisors large, asymmetrical, grossly serrate; left lacinia mobilis stemmed, distally cusped; accessory setal row well developed, without distal setal tuft, with more than 
<number box="[890,904,1183,1209]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="5.0">5</number>
accessory setae, with intermediate setae; molar a large, broad, weakly setose tongue. Maxilla 
<number box="[972,988,1223,1249]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="1.0">1</number>
: outer plate narrow with 
<number box="[1295,1323,1223,1249]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="11.0">11</number>
setal­teeth in compressed arrangement; palp 
<number box="[790,804,1263,1289]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="2.0">2</number>
­articulate. Maxilliped: outer plate with apical slender and robust setae, with medial robust setae; palp well­developed, unguis present. Gnathopod 
<number box="[502,517,1343,1369]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="1.0">1</number>
chelate; coxa reduced; posterior margin of propodus smooth; dactylus simple, without subterminal tooth. Gnathopod 
<number box="[853,871,1383,1409]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="2.0">2</number>
: posterodistal corner of propodus with medial setae. Pereopods 
<number box="[561,633,1423,1449]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="4.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="3.0">3 to 5</number>
simple; propodus without distal spurs. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
Pereopod 
<number box="[1236,1251,1422,1448]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="5.0">5</number>
basis expanded with large serrations on posterior margin.
</emphasis>
Pereopod 
<number box="[1080,1098,1463,1489]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="4.0">4</number>
: coxa deeper than wide, with large posteroventral lobe. Gills: from gnathopod 
<number box="[981,996,1503,1529]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="2.0">2</number>
to pereopod 
<number box="[1154,1170,1503,1529]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="7.0">7</number>
, not pleated. Uropod 
<number box="[361,376,1543,1569]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="3.0">3</number>
biramous, outer ramus 
<number box="[655,669,1543,1569]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="2.0">2</number>
­articulate. Telson cleft. (after 
<bibRefCitation author="Lowry" box="[1028,1319,1543,1569]" pageId="1" pageNumber="10" refString="Lowry, J. K. &amp; Stoddart, H. E. (1996) New Lysianassoid amphipod species from Namibia and Madagascar (Lysianassidae Dana, 1849 and Podoprionidae fam. nov.). Bolletino del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale, Verona, 20 (1993), 225 - 247." type="journal article" year="1996">
Lowry &amp; Stoddart, 
<number box="[1258,1319,1543,1569]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="1996.0">1996</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, bold 
<typeStatus box="[323,374,1583,1609]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">type</typeStatus>
indicates changes).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[264,1325,1022,1889]" box="[312,919,1622,1649]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,577,1622,1648]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Generic composition.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Chevreux, 1891" authorityName="Chevreux" authorityYear="1891" box="[584,915,1623,1649]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lysianassidae" genus="Podoprion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[584,709,1623,1648]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Podoprion</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Chevreux" box="[724,915,1623,1649]" pageId="1" pageNumber="10" refString="Chevreux, E. (1891) Voyage de la goelette Melita aux Canaries et au Senegal, 1889 - 1890. Podoprion bolivari, amphipode nouveau de la famille des Lysianassidae. Memoires de la Societe Zoologique de France. 4, 5 - 10, pl. 1." type="journal article" year="1891">
Chevreux, 
<number box="[853,915,1623,1649]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="1891.0">1891</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="2" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="1.[264,1325,1022,1889]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,452,1662,1688]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Etymology.</emphasis>
The family name was taken from the generic name 
<taxonomicName box="[1066,1192,1663,1688]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lysianassidae" genus="Podoprion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1066,1192,1663,1688]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Podoprion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Gr. 
<emphasis box="[1253,1315,1663,1688]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Podo</emphasis>
, meaning foot; Gr. 
<emphasis box="[479,602,1703,1728]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<taxonomicName box="[479,546,1703,1728]" class="Aves" family="Aves" genus="Prion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Aves" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Prion</taxonomicName>
–os,
</emphasis>
meaning saw) (
<bibRefCitation author="Lowry" box="[787,1081,1703,1729]" pageId="1" pageNumber="10" refString="Lowry, J. K. &amp; Stoddart, H. E. (1996) New Lysianassoid amphipod species from Namibia and Madagascar (Lysianassidae Dana, 1849 and Podoprionidae fam. nov.). Bolletino del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale, Verona, 20 (1993), 225 - 247." type="journal article" year="1996">
Lowry &amp; Stoddart, 
<number box="[1018,1081,1703,1729]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="1996.0">1996</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[264,1325,1022,1889]" box="[312,678,1742,1769]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,415,1742,1768]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Habitat.</emphasis>
Demersal scavengers.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="3" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[264,1325,1022,1889]" lastBlockId="2.[264,1323,284,510]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="3" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,433,1782,1808]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Remarks.</emphasis>
The family 
<taxonomicName authority="Lowry and Stoddart, 1996" authorityName="Lowry and Stoddart" authorityYear="1996" box="[584,1083,1783,1809]" class="Malacostraca" family="Podoprionidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">
Podoprionidae 
<bibRefCitation author="Lowry" box="[765,1083,1783,1809]" pageId="1" pageNumber="10" refString="Lowry, J. K. &amp; Stoddart, H. E. (1996) New Lysianassoid amphipod species from Namibia and Madagascar (Lysianassidae Dana, 1849 and Podoprionidae fam. nov.). Bolletino del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale, Verona, 20 (1993), 225 - 247." type="journal article" year="1996">
Lowry and Stoddart, 
<number box="[1022,1083,1783,1809]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="1996.0">1996</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, has an incisor process and an outer plate of maxilla 
<number box="[660,675,1823,1849]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="1.0">1</number>
that is unique among the lysianassoids (
<bibRefCitation author="Lowry" pageId="1" pageNumber="10" refString="Lowry, J. K. &amp; Stoddart, H. E. (1996) New Lysianassoid amphipod species from Namibia and Madagascar (Lysianassidae Dana, 1849 and Podoprionidae fam. nov.). Bolletino del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale, Verona, 20 (1993), 225 - 247." type="journal article" year="1996">
Lowry &amp; Stoddart, 
<number box="[326,389,1863,1889]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="1996.0">1996</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Three other genera have a chelate gnathopod 
<number box="[964,979,1863,1889]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="1.0">1</number>
similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[1110,1235,1863,1888]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lysianassidae" genus="Podoprion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1110,1235,1863,1888]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Podoprion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName authority="Boeck, 1876" authorityName="Boeck" authorityYear="1876" class="Malacostraca" family="Opisidae" genus="Opisa" kingdom="Animalia" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="3" order="Amphipoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1252,1322,1863,1888]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Opisa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Boeck" box="[264,416,284,310]" pageId="2" pageNumber="10" refString="Boeck, A. (1876) De Skandinaviske og Arktiske Amphipoder. Part 2. A. W. Brogger, Christiania, 161 - 713, pls. 8 - 32." type="book chapter" year="1876">
Boeck, 
<number box="[354,416,284,310]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="1876.0">1876</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName authority="Sars, 1895" authorityName="Sars" authorityYear="1895" box="[428,739,284,310]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lysianassidae" genus="Podoprionella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[428,604,284,309]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Podoprionella,</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Sars" box="[612,739,284,310]" pageId="2" pageNumber="10" refString="Sars, G. O. (1895) Amphipoda. In: An account of the Crustacea of Norway with Short Descriptions and Figures of all the Species. 711 pp, 240 plates, 8 supplementary plates. Christiania and Copenhagen (Cammermeyers)." type="book" year="1895">
Sars, 
<number box="[677,739,284,310]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="1895.0">1895</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName authority="Walker, 1906" authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1906" box="[752,1091,284,310]" class="Malacostraca" family="Opisidae" genus="Podoprionides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[752,924,284,309]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Podoprionides</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Walker" box="[932,1091,284,310]" pageId="2" pageNumber="11" refString="Walker, A. O. (1906) Preliminary descriptions of new species of Amphipoda from the Discovery Antarctic Expedition, 1902 - 1904. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, (Ser. 7), 17, 452 - 458." type="journal article" year="1906">
Walker, 
<number box="[1029,1091,284,310]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="1906.0">1906</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. The posterior margin of pereopod 
<number box="[464,479,324,350]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="5.0">5</number>
is armed with large serrations (
<quantity box="[863,940,324,350]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.778" metricValueMax="2.032" metricValueMin="1.524" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" unit="in" value="7.0" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="6.0">6–8 in</quantity>
the case of this species). Some species of 
<emphasis box="[388,752,364,389]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
Podoprionellla, 
<taxonomicName box="[580,752,364,389]" class="Malacostraca" family="Opisidae" genus="Podoprionides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Podoprionides</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, and some species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Costa, 1853" authorityName="Costa" authorityYear="1853" box="[1011,1267,364,390]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lysianassidae" genus="Ichnopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1011,1118,364,389]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Ichnopus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Costa" box="[1125,1267,364,390]" pageId="2" pageNumber="10" refString="Costa, A. (1853) Relazione sulla memoria del Dottor Achille Costa, di recherche su'crostacei amfipodi del regno di Napoli. Rendiconti dell'Accademia delle Science Fisiche e Matermatiche de Napoli. 2, 167 - 178." type="journal article" year="1853">
Costa, 
<number box="[1206,1267,364,390]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="1853.0">1853</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Clark &amp; Barnard, 1985" authorityName="Clark &amp; Barnard" authorityYear="1985" box="[264,854,404,430]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lysianassidae" genus="Socarnopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="catacumba">
<emphasis box="[264,544,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Socarnopsis catacumba</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Clark" box="[562,845,404,430]" pageId="2" pageNumber="10" refString="Clark, J. &amp; Barnard, J. L. (1985) Lucayarine catacumba, new genus, new species, a Bahamian seacave amphipod (Crustacea: Amphipoda: Lysianassidae). Proceeding sof the Biological Society of Washington, 98, 243 - 254." type="journal article" year="1985">
Clark &amp; Barnard, 
<number box="[783,845,404,430]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="1985.0">1985</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, have this character. However, in other respects these taxa are not closely related to 
<taxonomicName box="[810,935,444,469]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lysianassidae" genus="Podoprion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[810,935,444,469]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Podoprion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and therefore the allied generic names are misleading.
</paragraph>
